## Limitations

The research on the causes of being transgender is still evolving, with many studies limited by small sample sizes and a lack of longitudinal data. Additionally, the complexity of gender identity means that findings may not be universally applicable to all transgender individuals. There is also a risk of oversimplifying or misinterpreting the interplay between biological, environmental, and social factors. Further research is needed to deepen our understanding and to ensure that findings are inclusive of the diverse experiences within the transgender community.

